      "writtenOn": "2017-08-17T00:00:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s why I said \"in a previous CL perhaps\". I think we \u0027regressed\u0027 to per-request cache here: https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/5139ec72ee137a8524901ebd624bdb57bc7a5c38%5E%21/#F1\n\nI haven\u0027t looked too deep, but caching.ProcCache was likely using global proccache (which ultimately lives in global variable here https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/master/appengine/gaemiddleware/context.go#48), and caching.LRUBackend is using per-request LRU cache.\n\nI guess we can keep \"TODO: Switch to global LRU cache\" for now and switch to global LRU cache later, when https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/609369 (and a CL that injects it into default context) land.",
